20busy%20seasons%20that%20lasted%20several%20months%2C%20from%20January%20to%20March%2C%20and%20July%20to%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20first%20busy%20season%2C%20I%20was%20getting%20a%20lot%20less%20sleep.%20I%20went%20into%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week.%20Because%20I%20lived%20about%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20away%20from%20work%2C%20I'd%20have%20to%20get%20up%20early%20to%20get%20to%20work%20at%208%3A30%20a.m.%20I'd%20have%20my%20first%20meeting%20at%209%20a.m.%20and%20then%20either%20have%20back-to-back%20meetings%20or%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20Excel%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20I%20heard%20we%20were%20staying%20past%20dinner%2C%20I%20was%20fine%20with%20it.%20We%20were%20doing%20it%20as%20a%20team.%20There%20were%20days%20I'd%20get%20home%20around%2010%20or%2011%20p.m.%2C%20but%20it%20felt%20normal%20because%20co-workers%20I'd%20interned%20with%20were%20going%20through%20the%20same%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20few%20months%2C%20things%20calmed%20down%20and%20my%20routine%20was%20more%20like%20a%20normal%209-to-5%2C%20but%20halfway%20through%20the%20year%2C%20I%20was%20pulled%20into%20another%20busy%20season.%20I%20didn't%20feel%20prepared%20to%20go%20through%20it%20all%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20summer%2C%20and%20my%20friends%20would%20be%20at%20happy%20hours%20in%20the%20city.%20When%20the%20events%20were%20near%20my%20office%2C%20I'd%20go%20say%20hi%2C%20then%20have%20to%20go%20back%20to%20work%20while%20they%20enjoyed%20the%20sunshine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20joined%20PwC%2C%20I%20didn't%20realize%20I'd%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20two%20busy%20seasons%20in%20a%20year.%20The%20first%20time%20around%2C%20I%20stuck%20with%20it%20because%20I%20knew%20there%20would%20be%20hardships%20with%20any%20job%2C%20but%20the%20second%20time%20around%2C%20I%20realized%20the%20job%20wasn't%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20I'd%20work%20on%20weekends%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%20week%20ahead.%20I'd%20turn%20down%20invitations%20from%20friends%20to%20hang%20out.%20It%20felt%20like%20I%20couldn't%20enjoy%20the%20fruits%20of%20my%20labour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20try%20to%20maintain%20professionalism%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20but%20in%20private%2C%20I%20felt%20very%20emotional.%20When%20I%20told%20my%20parents%20about%20how%20I%20was%20struggling%2C%20they%20offered%20to%20help%20me%20look%20for%20new%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22acb6f7de-13b9-4500-bd52-27ef157ddc97%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20wanted%20more%20of%20a%20regular%209-to-5%20like%20my%20friends%20had%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20accounting%20professors%20advised%20me%20to%20double%20major%20so%20I'd%20have%20something%20to%20fall%20back%20on%2C%20because%20they%20were%20aware%20accounting%20isn't%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeveraging%20my%20second%20major%20in%20data%20analytics%2C%20I%20started%20applying%20to%20other%20jobs%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202024.%20I%20avoided%20accounting%20roles%20and%20looked%20specifically%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-analyst-non-tech-company-better-than-big-tech-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edata%20analyst%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20couple%20of%20weeks%2C%20I%20was%20invited%20to%20an%20interview%20with%20the%20media%20company%20Comcast.%20As%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20my%20interviewer%20was%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fey-accountant-13-years-big-four-career-lessons-learned-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eex-Big%20Four%20employee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20we%20connected%20over%20the%20struggles%20I%20experienced%20at%20PwC.%20He%20reassured%20me%20that%20I%20could%20expect%20more%20work-life%20balance%20if%20I%20worked%20at%20Comcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20completed%20the%20full%20interview%20process%20and%20started%20the%20role%20in%20November%202024.%20Once%20I%20received%20the%20offer%2C%20I%20resigned%20from%20PwC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20senior%20financial%20analyst%20at%20Comcast.%20They%20were%20looking%20for%20someone%20with%20Excel%20experience%20and%20tying%20out%20numbers%2C%20so%20I%20think%20my%20time%20at%20PwC%20helped%20me%20land%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247f777e8-d25c-4565-8c82-cf554faec781%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20have%20a%20better%20work-life%20balance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Comcast%2C%20my%20work%20schedule%20is%20more%20flexible.%20In%20auditing%2C%20during%20busy%20seasons%2C%20I'd%20sometimes%20work%20late%20into%20the%20evening%20or%20check%20my%20email%20at%20night%20to%20stay%20on%20top%20of%20deadlines%2C%20but%20I%20haven't%20had%20to%20do%20this%20in%20my%20current%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20breath%20of%20fresh%20air.%20I%20didn't%20realize%20this%20type%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-ceo-work-life-balance-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ework-life%20balance%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewas%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20benefits%20and%20emphasis%20on%20diversity%20and%20equality%20are%20quite%20similar%20across%20both%20companies%2C%20but%20the%20key%20difference%20has%20been%20the%20workload.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b2979f45-c9ff-4f3b-8409-f6f38526008f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20were%20upsides%20to%20working%20at%20the%20Big%20Four%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20more%20pros%20than%20cons%20to%20starting%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-be-successful-at-the-big-four-partners-advice-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecareer%20at%20the%20Big%20Four%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20get%20a%20very%20stable%20career%20path%2C%20and%20promotions%20are%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarting%20your%20career%20in%20an%20intense%20environment%20sets%20you%20up%20to%20work%20hard%20in%20your%20next%20role.%20The%20intense%20math%20and%20Excel%20skills%20I%20had%20to%20learn%20quickly%20at%20PwC%20serve%20me%20well%20at%20Comcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20con%20was%20the%20workload.%20I%20wasn't%20able%20to%20fulfill%20the%20work-life%20balance%20I'd%20imagined%20for%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20sectors%20within%20PwC%2C%20so%20my%20experience%20may%20not%20be%20the%20same%20as%20someone%20who%20worked%20in%20consulting%20or%20another%20area%20of%20the%20company.%20I'd%20consider%20going%20back%20to%20the%20Big%20Four%2C%20but%20not%20in%20audit.%20Maybe%20marketing%20or%20consulting%20might%20involve%20fewer%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20advice%20to%20others%20is%20to%20do%20what%20makes%20you%20happy%20and%20fulfills%20you.%20If%20it's%20not%20the%20Big%20Four%2C%20you%20can%20leave%20whenever%20you%20want%20and%20take%20control%20of%20your%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EComcast%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%20PwC%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20working%20at%20a%20Big%20Four%20firm%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Accheong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eccheong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-big-four-accounting-fortune-500-work-life-balance-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756214639000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68ad7340194a2d49b8af293a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-big-four-accounting-fortune-500-work-life-balance-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20Sofia%20Javier%20worked%20at%20PwC%20in%20auditing%2C%20she%20found%20%26quot%3Bbusy%20seasons%26quot%3B%20overwhelming.%20In%202024%2C%20she%20quit%20the%20Big%20Four%20to%20work%20for%20a%20Fortune%20500%20compan