mations%20Limited%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20monsoon%2C%20it%20was%20the%20same%20dreadful%20story.%20The%20water%20would%20not%20just%20flood%20the%20streets%3B%20it%20entered%20our%20homes%2C%20flowing%20right%20into%20the%20kitchen%20and%20living%20room.%20We%20were%20stranded%2C%20sometimes%20waist%E2%80%91deep%20in%20water%2C%20watching%20helplessly%20as%20our%20belongings%20were%20ruined.%20The%20floodwaters%20would%20remain%20for%20days%2C%20and%20often%2C%20the%20officials%20took%20time%20to%20help%20us%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20is%20the%20recall%20of%20Ratna%E2%80%AFDevi%20from%20Ward%E2%80%AFNo%E2%80%AF12%20in%20Ashoknagar.%20Her%20experience%20is%20not%20an%20isolated%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYear%20after%20year%2C%20this%20story%20echoed%20across%20Gorakhpur%E2%80%99s%20low-lying%20wards%2C%20where%20the%20monsoon%20heralded%20not%20renewal%20but%20ruin.%20Streets%20turned%20into%20rivers%2C%20daily%20life%20came%20to%20a%20halt%2C%20and%20residents%20waited%20anxiously%20amid%20rising%20waters%20and%20diminishing%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20felt%20like%20the%20monsoon%20was%20destroying%20our%20home.%E2%80%9D%20From%20June%20to%20September%2C%20residents%20feared%20waking%20up%20to%20flooded%20rooms%2C%20children%20forced%20to%20skip%20school%2C%20and%20personal%20belongings%20lost%20to%20murky%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EUnderstanding%20the%20flood%20problem%3A%20Terrain%2C%20drains%2C%20and%20urban%20growth%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGorakhpur%20is%20a%20saucer-shaped%20city.%20During%20rains%2C%20with%20no%20natural%20slope%20to%20guide%20drainage%2C%20floodwater%20lingers%2C%20and%20waterlogging%20persists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FBlue-and-Yellow