3EI%20didn't%20go%20to%20college.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-execs-just-joined-the-army-boot-camp-not-required-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejoined%20the%20Army%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%2018%20and%20served%20for%20nearly%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20got%20out%2C%20I%20worked%20the%20front%20desk%20at%20a%20gym.%20I%20kept%20seeing%20a%20group%20of%20guys%20who%20wore%20nice%20clothes%20and%20drove%20nice%20cars.%20I%20asked%20them%20what%20they%20did%20for%20work%2C%20and%20they%20told%20me%20they%20worked%20for%20CDW.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20I%20had%20no%20experience%20working%20in%20tech%2C%20they%20helped%20me%20get%20hired%20in%20tech%20sales.%20I%20went%20to%20work%20for%20CDW%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20continue%20my%20career%20at%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-amazon-early-years-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20HPE%2C%20Cisco%2C%20and%20Dell.%20Each%20had%20pros%20and%20cons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22956b4ae5-47ac-44f9-946d-530bfb170345%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20left%20CDW%20to%20work%20for%20SHI%20International%20Corp.%2C%20and%20then%20Dell%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20for%20SHI%20International%20Corp.%20for%20one%20year.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20my%20experience%20in%20the%20roles%20at%20CDW%20and%20SHI%2C%20I%20was%20hired%20as%20a%20sales%20manager%20at%20Dell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDell%20supported%20going%20back%20and%20getting%20your%20degree.%20It%20also%20had%20different%20mentorship%20groups%20to%20learn%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpresentation-tips-powerpoint-public-speaking-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epublic%20speaking%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20leadership%20development%2C%20especially%20for%20veterans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20headquarters%20in%20Round%20Rock%2C%20Texas%2C%20had%20all%20the%20major%20perks%2C%20such%20as%20lunches%2C%20snacks%2C%20and%20great%20offices%2C%20but%20I%20worked%20in%20one%20of%20their%20ancillary%20offices%20outside%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20get%20to%20experience%20those%20perks.%20I%20worked%20for%20Dell%20until%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220ca942af-923b-4d88-a185-21e6d5094c59%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfter%20Dell%2C%20I%20went%20to%20work%20for%20a%20company%20called%20Nimble%20Storage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20week%20after%20I%20started%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhewlett-packard-enterprise-ceo-drives-dei-commitment-against-industry-trends-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHPE%3C%2Fa%3E%20acquired%20Nimble.%20HPE%20gave%20me%20a%20car%20perk%2C%20great%20lunches%2C%20and%20tuition%20reimbursement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20HPE%2C%20I%20went%20to%20work%20for%20Cisco%20in%202018.%20The%20best%20benefit%20at%20Cisco%20was%20our%20global%20sales%20kickoff%20every%20year%20in%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20during%20which%20our%20company%20shut%20down%20most%20of%20Vegas%20for%20our%2020%2C000%20staff%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cool%20perks%20were%20things%20like%20the%20ability%20to%20get%20more%20technical%20certifications%20%E2%80%94%20Cisco%20has%20a%20very%20extensive%20training%20curriculum.%20They%20also%20had%20sales%20trainers%20come%20in%20and%20train%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Cisco%20didn't%20have%20the%20typical%20perks%20of%20other%20Big%20Tech%20companies%2C%20it%20had%20an%20amazing%20paternity%20and%20adoption%20program.%20Cisco%20gave%20you%20three%20weeks%20(outside%20your%20normal%20leave)%20to%20bond%20with%20your%20child.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECisco%20also%20had%20the%20best%20performance%20incentives%20for%20sales%20reps'%20compensation%20I've%20ever%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2237b90e54-7c06-434f-bdad-f56c19ccd3b6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20worked%20for%20Cisco%20until%20January%202019%20and%20left%20to%20work%20for%20Commvault%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20moved%20to%20Denver%20with%20my%20family%20and%20went%20to%20one%20of%20Cisco's%20partners%2C%20Commvault%2C%20a%20backup%20data%20protection%20company.%20While%20living%20in%20Denver%2C%20I%20contracted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamous-people-lyme-disease-diagnosis-symptoms-list%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELyme%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20we%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20D.C.%20area%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20needed%20a%20year%20to%20recover%2C%20and%20Commvault%20was%20very%20gracious%2C%20allowing%20me%20to%20have%20all%20the%20medical%20recovery%20time%20I%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb4a6dd6-6590-47eb-ae27-785966a1ff77%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmazon%20announced%20it%20was%20building%20a%20second%20HQ%20in%20the%20D.C.%20area%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20talking%20to%20colleagues%20I%20worked%20with%20at%20Cisco%20and%20Dell%2C%20and%20they%20suggested%20I%20apply%20to%20work%20at%20Amazon.%20Once%20I%20healed%20enough%20to%20work%20again%2C%20I%20went%20through%20the%20long%2C%20strenuous%20interview%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20step%20is%20to%20talk%20to%20a%20recruiter.%20The%20second%20stage%20is%20to%20speak%20to%20somebody%20in%20sales.%20Every%20interviewer%20asks%20questions%20associated%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-amazon-jobs-leadership-principles-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon's%2016%20leadership%20principles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20you%20go%20through%20that%20phase%2C%20you%20go%20through%20a%20process%20called%20a%20loop%20%E2%80%94%20a%20series%20of%20six%20interviews%20that%20you%20do%20on%20the%20same%20day.%20You%20have%20to%20tell%20a%20unique%20story%20for%20each%20leadership%20principle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20individuals%20in%20the%20loop%20is%20called%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fnews%2Fworkplace%2Famazon-job-interview-questions-tips-bar-raisers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebar%20raiser%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Their%20job%20is%20to%20ensure%20there%20are%20no%20unconscious%20biases%20in%20the%20interview%20process.%20The%20bar%20raiser%20comes%20from%20a%20completely%20different%20department%20%E2%80%94%20my%20bar%20raiser%20was%20one%20of%20the%20project%20managers%20for%20the%20Amazon%20recycling%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20one%20person%20finds%20anything%20challenging%2C%20they%20can%20put%20their%20thumbs%20down%20and%20say%20they%20don't%20vote%20for%20you%20joining%20the%20Amazon%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d4fe4d40-db8e-4cf7-9ac8-448848a735d0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20hired%20at%20Amazon%20in%20November%202021%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20became%20an%20account%20manager%20at%20Amazon.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20time%20in%20my%20career%20that%20I%20didn't%20sell%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20I%20sold%20a%20vision.%20I%20understood%20a%20client's%20vision%2C%20and%20then%20I%20would%20bring%20product%20market%20experts%20to%20help%20them%20define%20it%2C%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20build%20it%2C%20and%20ensure%20that%20it%20would%20hit%20their%20destinations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E30%25%20of%20my%20time%20was%20spent%20working%20with%20partners%2C%20preparing%20for%20different%20customer%20meetings%2C%20and%20having%20internal%20calls.%20Another%2020%25%20was%20spent%20bettering%20the%20AWS%20organization%20through%20mentorship%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20in%20person%20in%20Arlington%2C%20Virginia%2C%20or%20on%20a%20customer%20site%2C%20but%20I%20could%20also%20work%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270315147-3b86-4f4f-905f-814fda152ec4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmazon's%20second%20headquarters%20in%20Arlington%20is%20beautiful%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20multiple%20cuisine%20styles%20and%20restaurants%20with%20vegetarian%2C%20meat%2C%20and%20clean%20food%20options.%20There%20was%20also%20a%20game%20room%2C%20walkable%20gardens%2C%20quiet%20rooms%2C%20and%20a%20painting%20studio.%20I%20did%20cool%20arts%20and%20crafts%20with%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20building%20features%20solar%20panels%20on%20the%20rooftop%20and%20has%20gyms%2C%20bicycle%20parking%2C%20bicycle%20repair%20shops%2C%20and%20EV%20parking%20spaces%20with%20free%20charging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20is%20a%20dog-first%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20they%20have%20a%20dog%20run%20inside%20the%20building%20that's%20open%20to%20the%20public.%20There's%20just%20an%20aura%20when%20you're%20there%2C%20and%20it%20made%20me%20more%20productive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bcb09af7-bcb6-4ae2-9fea-9035f04c950b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20benefits%20at%20Amazon%20were%20lacking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E401(k)%20matching%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20health%20insurance%20were%20not%20as%20great%20as%20at%20other%20companies%20I%20worked%20for.%20One%20of%20the%20leadership%20principles%20is%20frugality.%20However%2C%20they%20did%20have%20the%20best%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployee-resource-groups-small-business-community-company-culture-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployee%20resource%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20can%20prove%20with%20data%20that%20something%20is%20true%2C%20they%20will%20implement%20a%20program%20for%20you.%20They%20allocated%20%241M%20to%20a%20program%20that%20gives%20free%20certifications%20to%20students%20at%20HBCUs%20and%20from%20marginalized%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20give%20you%20credits%20of%20up%20to%20%2420%2C000%2C%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20to%20help%20you%20through%20the%20adoption%20process%2C%20and%20give%20you%20paid%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f4e0aee-3cf1-4cd4-a845-ec4017284097%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20stayed%20at%20Amazon%20until%202024%2C%20when%20I%20decided%20to%20go%20into%20private%20equity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20in%20Big%20Tech%20is%20great%20if%20you%20have%20the%20personality%20fit%2C%20and%20I%20definitely%20have%20that%20personality.%20It%20also%20depends%20on%20which%20team%20you%20work%20on.%20I%20suggest%20working%20on%20growing%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%2C%20I%20realized%20that%2090%25%20of%20my%20customers%20were%20served%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-equity-careers-fundraising-investor-relations-skills-experiences-jobs-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprivate%20equity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20realization%20made%20me%20realize%20my%20true%20desire%20was%20to%20work%20in%20PE.%20I%20drive%20most%20portfolio%20companies%20to%20work%20with%20the%20Amazon%20team%2C%20so%20I%20still%20work%20with%20the%20same%20teams%20on%20a%20different%20side%20of%20the%20fence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22401018e3-c01d-47af-8b42-a15cb2cc4ae6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmazon%20has%20been%20my%20favorite%20place%20to%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20least%20favorite%20place%20to%20work%20was%20Dell%2C%20because%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20churn-and-burn%20factory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20place%20I%20worked%20was%20Amazon%20AWS%20because%20it%20was%20the%20most%20entrepreneurial%20place%20I'd%20ever%20worked.%20Every%20day%2C%20you%20were%20presented%20with%20unorthodox%20challenges%20internally%20and%20externally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20do%20the%20things%20I%20do%20now%20at%20the%20level%20I'm%20at%20without%20AWS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-work-experiences-amazon-hpe-cisco-dell-compare-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756199102000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68aca862cfc04e97619bf8c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3