ck-heading%5C%22%3ECarrying%20a%20family%E2%80%99s%20burden%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVaishali%E2%80%99s%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F486942%2Fharyana-teacher-beekeeping-business%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20journey%20to%20farming%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewas%20neither%20planned%20nor%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20passing%20in%202000%2C%20the%20responsibility%20of%20our%20farm%20fell%20on%20my%20brother%2C%20who%20was%20already%20battling%20alcoholism.%20When%20he%20died%20three%20years%20later%2C%20he%20left%20behind%20debts%20of%20Rs%2050%20lakhs%2C%20a%20widow%2C%20and%20two%20young%20children%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20just%2025%2C%20with%20a%20degree%20in%20Arts%20and%20a%20diploma%20in%20Business%20Management%2C%20Vaishali%20stepped%20in.%20She%20cleared%20the%20debts%2C%20rebuilt%20her%20family%E2%80%99s%20100-year-old%20home%2C%20and%20took%20charge%20of%20the%20farm.%20Just%20as%20stability%20returned%2C%20her%20mother%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20leukaemia%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20during%20this%20time%20that%20Vaishali%20came%20across%20%3Cstrong%3EKhapli%20wheat%20(Emmer%20wheat)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20an%20ancient%20grain%20once%20widely%20grown%20in%20India%20but%20nearly%20forgotten%20in%20modern%20agriculture.%20What%20drew%20her%20in%20were%20the%20many%20conversations%20around%20its%20health%20benefits.%20Unlike%20the%20modern%20wheat%20varieties%20commonly%20found%20in%20markets%2C%20Khapli%20was%20said%20to%20be%20richer%20in%20fibre%20and%20nutrients%2C%20easier%20to%20digest%2C%20and%20gentler%20on%20people%20with%20chronic%20illnesses.%20It%20was%20also%20believed%20to%20release%20energy%20slowly%20into%20the%20body%2C%20making%20it%20a%20better%20choice%20for%20those%20who%20struggled%20with%20fluctuating%20blood%20sugar%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Vaishali%2C%20whose%20mother%E2%80%99s%20fragile%